<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Portfolio | lisAIconsulting</title>
  <meta
    name="description"
    content="Portfolio examples from lisAIconsulting, including practical AI and automation work."
  />
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow">Portfolio</p>
        <h1>Selected Examples of Delivery and Automation Work</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          This page highlights practical examples of work that combine program delivery,
          process improvement, and automation. These samples are intended to show how
          structured execution and lightweight tooling can improve visibility, reduce
          manual effort, and support scalable business operations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="portfolio-item">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Defect Tracking Automation (n8n)</h2>
        <p>
          A lightweight workflow automation designed to improve how teams capture,
          organize, and track defects using a structured intake process and centralized log.
        </p>

        <div class="portfolio-summary">
          <div class="summary-card">
            <h3>Problem</h3>
            <p>
              Teams often rely on scattered emails, chat messages, or manual spreadsheets
              to report and track defects, creating inconsistent intake and limited visibility.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="summary-card">
            <h3>Solution</h3>
            <p>
              Built an automated defect intake and tracking workflow using n8n, connected
              to a form-based submission process and Google Sheets for centralized logging.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="summary-card">
            <h3>Outcome</h3>
            <p>
              Created a more consistent and trackable process that improves visibility,
              reduces manual handling, and supports better follow-through on issue management.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="portfolio-section">
          <h3>Workflow Overview</h3>
          <p>
            The workflow begins with a defect submission, routes through n8n for handling
            and formatting, and records the issue in a centralized tracker for review and follow-up.
          </p>

          <div class="workflow-diagram">
            <div class="workflow-step">User submits defect form</div>
            <div class="workflow-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="workflow-step">n8n workflow triggered</div>
            <div class="workflow-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="workflow-step">Data validation and formatting</div>
            <div class="workflow-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="workflow-step">Defect logged to Google Sheet</div>
            <div class="workflow-arrow">↓</div>
            <div class="workflow-step">Team visibility and follow-up</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="portfolio-section">
          <h3>Sample Screens</h3>
          <p>
            These visuals show the structure of the workflow and the output used for tracking.
          </p>

          <div class="image-grid">
            <figure class="image-card">
              <img src="/images/portfolio/defect-tracker-workflow.png" alt="n8n defect tracking workflow" />
              <figcaption>n8n workflow</figcaption>
            </figure>

            <figure class="image-card">
              <img src="/images/portfolio/defect-tracker-form.png" alt="Defect intake form" />
              <figcaption>Defect intake form</figcaption>
            </figure>

            <figure class="image-card">
              <img src="/images/portfolio/defect-tracker-sheet.png" alt="Google Sheet defect tracker output" />
              <figcaption>Centralized defect tracker</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="portfolio-section">
          <h3>What This Example Demonstrates</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Practical workflow design for operational process improvement</li>
            <li>Use of lightweight automation tools to reduce manual effort</li>
            <li>Clear intake and tracking structure for better visibility</li>
            <li>Ability to connect business need, process flow, and working output</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="portfolio-cta">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Interested in Similar Work?</h2>
        <p>
          lisAIconsulting supports organizations that need practical help with AI programs,
          automation opportunities, governance, and delivery execution.
        </p>
        <a class="button" href="/contact">Contact Me</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
